.Hl "[FAQ Index]" faq - .
.\">>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
.ds Qu "New functionality; what is useful to me as an old MicroEmacs user ??
.ds Qn 00
.NH faq\*(Qn page "FAQ(\*(Qn) \- \*(Qu"
.XI faq\*(Qn 0f "\*(Qu"
.ne 10
.SH "QUESTION (\*(Qn)"
\*(Qu
.SH ANSWER
There are a lot of new features in this  distribution.  Assuming that you just
want to use the  editor  (and have  cottoned  onto the fact that there are now
scroll bars etc.) then the most frequent commands that we use are:-
.BS
.Ht grep 3
\- May need to set up in \fI<user>.emf\fR.
.BU
.Ht diff 3
\- May need to set up in \fI<user>.emf\fR.
.BU
.Ht compile 3
\- May need to set up in \fI<user>.emf\fR.
.BU
.Ht clean 3
\- cleans a buffer, removing spaces etc.
.BU
.Ht restyle-buffer 3
\- Reformats 'C' + known languages.
.BU
.Ht spell-buffer 3
\- For documentation work, spells the buffer.
.BU
\fBC-s\fR \-
.Ht isearch-forward 2
incremental search.
.BU
\fBC-x u\fR or \fCC-_\fR \-
.Ht undo 2
undoes edits.
.BU
\fBF10\fR \-
.Ht file-browser 3
allows the file system to be browsed
.BE
Other useful macros include:-
.BS
.Ht tabs-to-spaces 3
\- Good for sorting out the mess made by Microsoft Developer Studio.
.BU
.Ht sort-lines 2
\- Two versions of this, allows marked lines to be sorted alphabetically.
.BE
Be wary of:-
.BS
\fBesc-o\fR
\-
.Ht fill-paragraph 2 .
The  default  mode is an  automatic
mode which attempts to guess at the format required.
It works most of the time. Also works in 'C'.
.BE
Most of the other new  features are in the  background,  such as the macro
processor,  indentation  control, color hilighting,  indentation control,
auto-saving etc.
.PP
