.ds Qu "C++ is not default, C is - how do I change this ??
.ds Qn 02
.NH faq\*(Qn page "FAQ(\*(Qn) \- \*(Qu"
.XI faq\*(Qn 0f "\*(Qu"
.ne 10
.SH "QUESTION (\*(Qn)"
\*(Qu
.SH ANSWER
If your main programming language is C++, then you will require the \fC.def\fR
and \fC\.h\fR  files to be loaded in C++ mode by default,  rather than 'C'. To
modify this hen the order of the file hooks has to be re-defined.
.PP
Within your  \fI<user>.emf\fR,  over-ride the default  ordering by including the
line:-
.Me $emf-scheme
.CS
add-file-hook ".h .def"                                     fhook-cpp
.CE
.Me $ehf-scheme
This adds a newer binding for "\fC.h\fR" and "\fC.def\fR" to C++,  over-riding
the existing 'C' binding.
.PP
