.ds Qu "me32.ini - Where does it go, how do I know it's being processed ??
.ds Qn 23
.NH faq\*(Qn page "FAQ(\*(Qn) \- \*(Qu"
.XI faq\*(Qn 0f "\*(Qu"
.ne 10
.SH "QUESTION (\*(Qn)"
\*(Qu
.SH ANSWER
Question posed as:-
.CS
> 1)  Am I right in assuming that for NT the file me32.ini goes
>     into  %windir%, i.e. into c:\winnt ?
.CE
Yes, this is where the other .ini files are.
.CS
> 2)  How do I know me32.ini is being processed?  Creating one,
>     as described in the readme.txt file doesn't seem to have
>     any visible effect.
.CE
From within the editor, if you show the variable
.Ht $MEPATH 5 ,
then it should echo the paths that you have defined in the me32.ini file.
.CS
esc-x describe-variable
$MEPATH
.CE
See:
.Ht me32.ini 8 ,
.Hl "Installation Information" Installation 1 ,
.Hl "Setting Up A User Profile" UserProfiles 2 .
.CS
> 3) What does the "fontfile" statement do ?
