disable the \fBTab To Indent\fR option in
.Ht user-setup 3
i.e.
.IP
\fBHelp\fR -> \fBUser Setup\fR -> \fBGeneral\fR -> \fBTab To Indent\fR
.LP
This  enables  the  use of the TAB key in all  column  positions  with  the
exception of column 0. A <tab> in Column 0 will still enable the  automatic
line re-formatting.
.PP
If you want real <Tabs> then disable the \fBtab\fR mode using
.Ht user-setup 3
i.e.
.IP
\fBHelp\fR -> \fBUser Setup\fR -> \fBGeneral\fR -> \fBTab\fR
.SS "To change the 'C' Indentation Layout"
